ul.li: Width of the ribbon path represent the size of outgoing movement from the location.
Color of the ribbon paths connecting two locations follow the color of the location in which net incoming movements is greater.Â

For example, if movement from location A to location B is greater than movement from B to A which indicates that the incoming movement to B is greater, the color of the ribbon path connecting A and B would follow the color of location B
